What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Wound Irrigation Systems Market?



Market Analysis and Size

Wound irrigation systems are medical devices used to clean and irrigate wounds during the wound care process. They are designed to remove debris, bacteria, and foreign particles from the wound site to promote healing and reduce the risk of infection. There are several types of wound irrigation systems available, and the choice of system depends on the nature and severity of the wound.

Data Bridge Market Research analyzes that the global wound irrigation systems market which was USD 285.67 million in 2022, would rocket up to USD 359.08 million by 2030, and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 2.9% during the forecast period. The manual segment is expected to dominate the type segment of the market owing to the increasing prevalence of wound irrigation systems.

